ing from a third party or travel agent, then this does not apply to the web check-in process.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>The process of online check-in closes 45 minutes before departure time if you have a scheduled flight.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>How Early Can You Check in with Etihad Airways?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to get the information related to how early you can check in with Etihad, then for that, you are required to know that the Etihad check-in counters open up three hours before the scheduled departure. And, if you are in Abu Dhabi, then four hours from flight time. Also, check-in closes 60 minutes before departure, and for diamond first class and perls business class passengers in Abu Dhabi, check-in closes at least 45 minutes before departure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Etihad Airways Ticket Check</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to check your ticket, then use the flight PNR number for confirmations, the origin and destination information, flight number, and arrival &amp; departure timing. You can also check the status of your flight by using the PNR and check the status which can help you plan the travel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Etihad Airways Baggage Check-in</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you complete your web check-in process, then Etihad baggage rules allow you to drop the check-in baggage. If you don&#39;t check in your luggage, navigate to the area and head straight to the security counter. Also, you must reach the airport at least 2 hours before the scheduled departure for any late inconveniences. If you have no check-in luggage, you can directly head out for the security check and board your flight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Etihad Web Check-in Online</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to know the process for Etihad web check-in online and this is used to get the boarding pass on your device, then for that, below are the following all the steps that are mentioned, and you need to follow all the below-mentioned steps:-</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>I